{
  "info": {
    "name": "Pierflow API",
    "description": "End-to-end working set for the Pierflow partner-facing API. Two product surfaces:\n\n## Records API (folders 1–10)\n  1–8 walk the records lifecycle: create a scan batch, upload via signed Cloudinary URL, register an ingest job, poll, list patients, download + acknowledge an import package.\n  9    PartnerPatientLink CRUD — register mappings between Pierflow's patient id and your EMR's id.\n  10   By-external FHIR shortcut — query Pierflow with **your own** patient id.\n\n## Insurance API (folders 11–14)\n  11   Plans — browse the catalogue with filters; retrieve one plan.\n  12   Quotes — submit a user profile, get back ranked + priced quotes valid for 24 hours.\n  13   Enrollments — convert a quote into a real HMO policy; confirm payment; cancel.\n  14   HMO Network — list all HMOs with rate cards; opt in/out to control which HMOs appear in Plans + Quotes.\n\nRun the Records folders in order. The Insurance folders run top-to-bottom: Plans populates `plan_id`, Quotes populates `quote_id`, Enrollments uses both. The whole insurance chain can be exercised end-to-end against the sandbox stub connector.\n\n## Setup\n1. Open this collection's Variables tab.\n2. Set `base_url` (default `https://www.pierflow.com`).\n3. Set `api_key` (issue one from `/portal/keys` in your partner portal).\n4. For Records calls, set `organization_id` to an org you're linked to.\n5. For Insurance calls, set `provider_slug` to an HMO you're consuming from (optional).\n\n## Auth\nEvery request sends `Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}`. Records calls need the `records:read` scope; Insurance calls need `insurance:read`. Legacy keys (empty scopes) are granted all scopes.\n\n## Money\nAll monetary fields are in NGN minor units (kobo). 850000 = ₦8,500. BigInts arrive as strings — parse explicitly.\n\n## Docs\n- Records: https://www.pierflow.com/docs/patient-mapping\n- Plans: https://www.pierflow.com/docs/plans\n- Quotes: https://www.pierflow.com/docs/quotes",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "https://www.pierflow.com",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "api_key",
      "value": "pf_test_sk_REPLACE_ME",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "organization_id",
      "value": "REPLACE_ME",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "sample_image_url",
      "value": "https://www.pierflow.com/sample-outpatient-card.svg",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "batch_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "job_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "patient_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "package_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "upload_url",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "upload_folder",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "upload_timestamp",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "upload_signature",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "upload_api_key",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "cloudinary_public_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "cloudinary_secure_url",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "external_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "provider_slug",
      "value": "reliance-hmo",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "plan_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "quote_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "quote_request_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "enrollment_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "fintech_user_ref",
      "value": "user_pmsmoke_001",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{api_key}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1 · Setup",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List organizations I can act on",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/organizations",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "organizations"]
            },
            "description": "Returns every ACTIVE organization your API key has a PartnerOrganizationLink to. If this is empty, register a customer org from /portal/organizations and ask Pierflow staff to approve it."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has at least one org', () => pm.expect(body).to.be.an('array').and.have.length.greaterThan(0));",
                  "// Auto-fill organization_id if not set yet",
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('organization_id') || pm.collectionVariables.get('organization_id') === 'REPLACE_ME') {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('organization_id', body[0].id);",
                  "  console.log('Set organization_id =', body[0].id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2 · Create a scan batch",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/scan-batches",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"organizationId\": \"{{organization_id}}\",\n  \"label\": \"Smoke test via Postman\",\n  \"priority\": \"NORMAL\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/scan-batches",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "scan-batches"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a ScanBatch that subsequent uploads will be grouped under. Batches are how reviewers and the package builder treat a set of pages as a unit."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('batch_id', body.batch_id);",
                  "console.log('Set batch_id =', body.batch_id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3 · Sign a Cloudinary upload",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/uploads/sign",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"organizationId\": \"{{organization_id}}\",\n  \"batchId\": \"{{batch_id}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/uploads/sign",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "uploads", "sign"]
            },
            "description": "Returns a one-shot Cloudinary upload signature. Your client uploads the file directly to Cloudinary using these fields — Pierflow never touches the bytes."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('upload_url', body.uploadUrl);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('upload_folder', body.folder);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('upload_timestamp', String(body.timestamp));",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('upload_signature', body.signature);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('upload_api_key', body.apiKey);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "4 · Upload to Cloudinary (multipart)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST {{upload_url}} (form-data, file)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": { "raw": "{{upload_url}}", "host": ["{{upload_url}}"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "description": "Attach an image file here. The first time you run this in Postman, click 'Select Files' and pick a JPG / PNG. For automated runs, use a hosted image and switch this request to a 'remote URL' form field — Cloudinary supports both."
                },
                { "key": "api_key", "value": "{{upload_api_key}}" },
                { "key": "timestamp", "value": "{{upload_timestamp}}" },
                { "key": "folder", "value": "{{upload_folder}}" },
                { "key": "type", "value": "upload" },
                { "key": "signature", "value": "{{upload_signature}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Posts the file straight to Cloudinary using the signature we just got. Returns `public_id` and `secure_url` we hand back to Pierflow on the next step.\n\n**Why not URL upload?** Postman's multipart limits make local-file uploads the most reliable path. If you want to ingest a hosted image without uploading bytes, change the 'file' field's key to 'file' and value to `{{sample_image_url}}` (no file selected) — Cloudinary will pull from the URL."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('cloudinary_public_id', body.public_id);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('cloudinary_secure_url', body.secure_url);",
                  "console.log('Uploaded', body.public_id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "5 · Register the ingest job",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/ingest/documents",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"organizationId\": \"{{organization_id}}\",\n  \"batchId\": \"{{batch_id}}\",\n  \"source\": {\n    \"publicId\": \"{{cloudinary_public_id}}\",\n    \"secureUrl\": \"{{cloudinary_secure_url}}\"\n  },\n  \"documentType\": \"OUTPATIENT_CARD\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/ingest/documents",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "ingest", "documents"]
            },
            "description": "Tells Pierflow the asset exists. We return 202 immediately and run extraction asynchronously. Use the job_id returned here to poll for completion."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 202', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('job_id', body.job_id);",
                  "console.log('Set job_id =', body.job_id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "6 · Poll the job",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/ingest/jobs/:jobId",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/ingest/jobs/{{job_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "ingest", "jobs", "{{job_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the current ProcessingJob state. Re-run this every few seconds until status moves out of QUEUED / PROCESSING to AWAITING_REVIEW or VALIDATED."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "console.log('Job status:', body.status);",
                  "// If the job has produced an extracted record matched to a patient,",
                  "// pick up the patient_id so subsequent requests have it.",
                  "const matched = (body.records || []).find(r => r.patient_id);",
                  "if (matched) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('patient_id', matched.patient_id);",
                  "  console.log('Set patient_id =', matched.patient_id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "7 · Patients",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/organizations/:orgId/patients",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/organizations/{{organization_id}}/patients",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "organizations", "{{organization_id}}", "patients"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (Array.isArray(body) && body.length > 0 && !pm.collectionVariables.get('patient_id')) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('patient_id', body[0].id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/organizations/:orgId/patients/:patientId/fhir",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/organizations/{{organization_id}}/patients/{{patient_id}}/fhir",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "organizations",
                "{{organization_id}}",
                "patients",
                "{{patient_id}}",
                "fhir"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns a merged FHIR R4 Bundle covering every validated ExtractedRecord on this patient."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "8 · Import packages",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/organizations/:orgId/import-packages",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/organizations/{{organization_id}}/import-packages",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "organizations",
                "{{organization_id}}",
                "import-packages"
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "const ready = (Array.isArray(body) ? body : []).find(p => p.status === 'READY');",
                  "if (ready) pm.collectionVariables.set('package_id', ready.id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/import-packages/:packageId/download",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/import-packages/{{package_id}}/download",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "import-packages", "{{package_id}}", "download"]
            },
            "description": "Returns a short-lived signed Cloudinary URL pointing at the ZIP."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/import-packages/:packageId/acknowledge",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"imported_patient_count\": 1,\n  \"failed_patient_ids\": [],\n  \"failure_reasons\": {},\n  \"partner_import_reference\": \"emr-import-{{$timestamp}}\",\n  \"patient_id_mappings\": [\n    {\n      \"pierflow_patient_id\": \"{{patient_id}}\",\n      \"external_id\": \"emr_patient_{{$randomInt}}\",\n      \"external_system\": \"https://your-emr.example.com/patients/\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/import-packages/{{package_id}}/acknowledge",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "import-packages",
                "{{package_id}}",
                "acknowledge"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Acknowledges receipt of an import package. Successfully imported records get marked IMPORTED and won't ship again. Failed patient ids stay packaged so the next cron picks them up.\n\n**patient_id_mappings (optional)** — pairs of (pierflow_patient_id, external_id) the partner's EMR created during import. Each becomes a PartnerPatientLink with source IMPORT_ACK so future API calls can target the patient via /v1/organizations/:orgId/patients/by-external/:externalId/fhir. Per-item results return in the response so partners retry only failures."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "9 · Partner patient links",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/partner-patient-links (by MRN)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"kind\": \"by_mrn\",\n  \"organization_id\": \"{{organization_id}}\",\n  \"mrn\": \"LH-00143-26\",\n  \"external_id\": \"emr_patient_8821\",\n  \"external_system\": \"https://your-emr.example.com/patients/\",\n  \"placeholder_name\": \"Adaeze Margaret Nwosu\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/partner-patient-links",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "partner-patient-links"]
            },
            "description": "Register a mapping between the partner's external_id and a Pierflow Patient resolved via MRN. If no Patient has that MRN yet, we create a placeholder Patient + identifier + link so future extracted records auto-attach. `placeholder_name` is only used when we have to create that placeholder.\n\nIdempotent on (partner, patient) and (partner, external_id) — re-posting the same pair returns the existing link."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('patient_id', body.patient_id);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('external_id', body.external_id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/partner-patient-links (by patient id)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"kind\": \"by_patient_id\",\n  \"organization_id\": \"{{organization_id}}\",\n  \"patient_id\": \"{{patient_id}}\",\n  \"external_id\": \"emr_patient_8821\",\n  \"external_system\": \"https://your-emr.example.com/patients/\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/partner-patient-links",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "partner-patient-links"]
            },
            "description": "Direct link to an existing Pierflow Patient by its id. Use this after you've imported records and gotten back a Pierflow patient_id in a package manifest."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/partner-patient-links/bulk",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"organization_id\": \"{{organization_id}}\",\n  \"external_system\": \"https://your-emr.example.com/patients/\",\n  \"items\": [\n    { \"kind\": \"by_mrn\", \"mrn\": \"LH-00143-26\", \"external_id\": \"emr_8821\" },\n    { \"kind\": \"by_mrn\", \"mrn\": \"LH-00200-26\", \"external_id\": \"emr_8822\", \"placeholder_name\": \"Tunde Adeleke\" },\n    { \"kind\": \"by_patient_id\", \"patient_id\": \"{{patient_id}}\", \"external_id\": \"emr_8823\" }\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/partner-patient-links/bulk",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "partner-patient-links", "bulk"]
            },
            "description": "Cohort-import friendly: post up to 500 mapping items in one call. Mix `by_mrn` and `by_patient_id` flavours freely. Response includes per-item ok/reason so you retry only the failures."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/partner-patient-links?external_id=…",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/partner-patient-links?external_id={{external_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "partner-patient-links"],
              "query": [{ "key": "external_id", "value": "{{external_id}}" }]
            },
            "description": "Look up a link by either side. Accepts ?external_id=… or ?patient_id=…. Returns 404 if no link exists."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "10 · FHIR by external id",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/organizations/:orgId/patients/by-external/:externalId/fhir",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/organizations/{{organization_id}}/patients/by-external/{{external_id}}/fhir",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "organizations",
                "{{organization_id}}",
                "patients",
                "by-external",
                "{{external_id}}",
                "fhir"
              ]
            },
            "description": "EMR-vendor convenience: query Pierflow with **your own** patient id and get back the merged FHIR Bundle. We resolve the PartnerPatientLink internally, so your EMR doesn't need to maintain a mapping table. Patient.identifier in the response includes your external id (use: secondary) so round-trips are self-describing."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Bundle has Patient.identifier with our external id', () => {",
                  "  const patient = body.entry.find(e => e.resource.resourceType === 'Patient');",
                  "  pm.expect(patient).to.exist;",
                  "  const idents = patient.resource.identifier || [];",
                  "  const externalSeen = idents.some(i => i.value === pm.collectionVariables.get('external_id'));",
                  "  pm.expect(externalSeen).to.be.true;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "11 · Plans",
      "description": "Browse the HMO plan catalogue. Universal Plan Schema. Requires `insurance:read` scope.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List plans",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/v1/plans?limit=10&status=ACTIVE",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "plans"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "limit", "value": "10" },
                { "key": "status", "value": "ACTIVE" },
                {
                  "key": "scope",
                  "value": "INDIVIDUAL",
                  "disabled": true,
                  "description": "INDIVIDUAL | FAMILY | EMPLOYEE_GROUP | STUDENT | OTHER"
                },
